        <h3><a href="https://www.dukechronicle.com/article/2019/03/duke-mens-basketball-zion-williamson-near-perfect-in-return-acc-tournament">&#039;A crazy different type of player&#039;: Zion Williamson makes it look easy with near-perfect performance in return</a></h3>
                    </article>

                                                                                                </div>
                        

                        <p>Back in late November 2017, in a <a href="https://youtu.be/mYgko5itMY0?t=191">video posted on his YouTube channel</a>, Durant talked highly of the recent addition to the NBA.</p>
<p>“Cam Reddish. Athletic. Long arms. Quick in transition,” Durant said in the video. “This kid can be a pro if he put the work in for sure. Nice turn-around J. Wow.</p>
<p>“His athleticism’s off the charts. You can spin and keep going and finish at the rim like that,” Durant said as he shook his head. “Next level.”</p>
<p>To conclude his remarks, the two-time NBA Finals Most Valuable Player left the Reddish portion of the video with a bold prediction for the future of the then-high schooler.</p>
<p>“I like this kid,” Durant said. “He’s going to be a star.”</p>
